<!DOCTYPE html PUBLIC "-//W3C//DTD XHTML 1.0 Strict//EN" "http://www.w3.org/TR/xhtml1/DTD/xhtml1-strict.dtd">
<html xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml">
<head>
<title>CSS Test: column-gap</title>
<link rel="author" title="Hakon Wium Lie" href="mailto:howcome@opera.com"/>
<link rel="help" href="http://www.w3.org/TR/css3-multicol/#column-gap"/>
<link rel="match" href="multicol-gap-000-ref.xht"/>
<meta name="flags" content="ahem" />
<style type="text/css">
div.multicol { 
  font: 10px/10px Ahem;
  margin: 1em 0;
  background: yellow;
  width: 600px;
  column-width: 200px;
  column-gap: 200px;
  column-rule: none;
}
div.ref {
  font: 10px/10px Ahem;
  margin: 1em 0;
  color: black;
  width: 600px;
}
div.ref span { color: yellow }
</style>
</head>
<body>
The two horizontal bars below should be identical.
<div class="multicol">01234567890123456789<br/>01234567890123456789</div>
<div class="ref">01234567890123456789<span>01234567890123456789</span>01234567890123456789</div>
</body>
</html>
